    {
      "type": "edit",
      "id": "0549f26bc6a8ab01",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "0549f26bc6a8ab01",
        "text": "We are only repeating the standard question that must always and everywhere impose itself on this last group when we consider how this could happen. The process is clearly against the will of the majority, the result is unfavorable for the majority. It does not have to go that way, but it can - as everyone knows - go that way. The minority, absurdly enough, has a chance to impose its new order. How, in what is this chance founded?"
