        "text": "2 The emergence of legitimacy from the principle of reciprocity.\n\nThe path to the further expansion of power is probably largely mapped out: a part of the negatively privileged majority is brought into direct dependence, drawn into the relations of wage-performance or protection-obedience (creation of a service class). This later phase will be examined in more detail following the second and third examples. Here we shall first be interested in a phenomenon which can already be observed in the beginning of the formation of power and which also contributes to the explanation of the absurd assertiveness of the new group: a process which one could call the generatio aequivoca of legitimacy.\n"
